# Documentation rules

- Write for a reader who has no conversation context; lead with purpose and authoritative status.
- Use the exact domain vocabulary from the Architecture Bible and link rather than duplicate source material.
- Separate current behavior, target architecture, and roadmap; never present plans as implemented facts.
- Prefer short sections, decision tables, and Mermaid only when relationships benefit from a visual.
- Give commands and paths that are verified against the repository.
- Date audit snapshots and identify owners or review triggers for durable documents.
- Do not include secrets, private operational notes, or unsupported performance claims.
